You don’t get injured by doing exercises your body is physically capable of doing..

You injure yourself through :
-being physically incapable to perform said exercises and still do it anyways
-using terrible form that jeopardizes the mechanical movements of your body
-repetitive use can cause injury too 

For the most part there is a general “form” for each exercise but EVERYONE performs that ideal form with a slight alteration. Why the hell cant Dirk Navinksi run with the same form as Usain Bolt? Hmm 🤔 maybe because their built different. 

Cross fit doesn’t destroy or wreck bodies UNLESS...UNLESS you have zero experience and just jump right into it without building up your body to be able to handle said exercises. If you build yourself up slowly and correctly, I see no reason why this will spontaneously destroy someone’s body-unless you do anyone of the reasons mentioned above.

Give yourself plenty of rest-let each muscle group rest from time to time so you don’t cause a repetitive strain injury. Stretch stretch stretch and don’t do something you physically can’t do. That goes for ANY sport
You promote speed over form. Anyone could do this, and when done right then they will grow in strength. Shame on you
